<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="typeid" id="typeid">typeid</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="kw2">typeid</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> object <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>

The typeid operator returns a reference to a <a href="../typeinfo/start#type_info" class="wikilink1" title="typeinfo:start">type_info</a> object that describes
`object`.
</p>

<p>
If `object` is a null pointer, then the operation will throw a <a href="../typeinfo/start#bad_cast" class="wikilink1" title="typeinfo:start">std::bad_typeid</a> exception.
</p>

<p>
<strong>NOTE</strong> The C++98 standard requires that header file <code>&lt;typeinfo&gt;</code> to be included before operator typeid is used within a compilation unit. Otherwise, the program is considered ill-formed.
</p>

</div>
